{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Say hi to me\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}], \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929", "id": "msg_018s8hS1cQ4JYmXt7TnEshMH", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hi! I'm Sculptor, your AI coding assistant. I'm here to help you with writing code, fixing bugs, and answering questions about your codebase.\n\nI can see you're working on branch_1 in your repository. How can I help you today?"}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 3, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 18055, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 18055, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 61, "service_tier": "standard"}}}
{"key": "{\"messages\": [{\"content\": [{\"text\": \"Warmup\", \"type\": \"text\"}], \"role\": \"user\"}], \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929\", \"stop\": null, \"temperature\": 1.0, \"top_k\": null, \"top_p\": null}", "value": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-5-20250929", "id": "msg_013maPTjPVC6aJTUVn6TYnpr", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hello! I'm Claude Code, ready to help you explore codebases and design implementation plans.\n\nI'm currently in **READ-ONLY planning mode**, which means I can:\n- \u2705 Explore the codebase using `Glob`, `Grep`, and `Read` tools\n- \u2705 Run read-only bash commands (ls, cat, git log, find, etc.)\n- \u2705 Design detailed implementation plans\n- \u2705 Identify critical files and patterns\n\nBut I **cannot**:\n- \u274c Create, modify, or delete files\n- \u274c Run commands that change system state\n- \u274c Install packages or dependencies\n\nLet me start by getting familiar with your codebase structure:\n\n<function_calls>\n<invoke name=\"bash\">\n<parameter name=\"command\">find /code -type f -name \"*.py\" -o -name \"*.js\" -o -name \"*.ts\" -o -name \"*.json\" -o -name \"*.md\" | head -20</parameter>\n</invoke>\n</function_calls>\n<function_calls>\n<invoke name=\"bash\">\n<parameter name=\"command\">ls -la /code</parameter>\n</invoke>\n</function_calls>\n<function_calls>\n<invoke name=\"read\">\n<parameter name=\"path\">/code</parameter>\n</invoke>\n</function_calls>\n\nI'm ready to help! What would you like me to explore or design? Please provide:\n1. The requirements or feature you'd like me to plan\n2. Any specific perspective or approach you'd like me to take\n\nI'll thoroughly explore the codebase, understand existing patterns, and create a detailed implementation plan for you."}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "stop_sequence": null, "usage": {"input_tokens": 953, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0, "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0}, "output_tokens": 447, "service_tier": "standard"}}}
